## Common Symptoms

- **Squealing or squeaking** when braking — often the wear indicator making first contact with the rotor
- **Grinding noise** under braking — pads are worn through; metal-on-metal contact with the rotor
- **Soft or spongy pedal** that travels further than normal before the brakes engage
- **Pulsation or vibration** through the pedal or steering wheel when slowing down
- **Vehicle pulling to one side** during braking
- **Brake warning light** on the dashboard (separate from the parking brake light)

